checker

Class TypeChecker

  • java.lang.Object
    • checker.TypeChecker

  • public class TypeChecker
extends java.lang.Object
    The TypeChecker class provides methods to check and manipulate the types of objects. It includes methods to verify if an object can be parsed as a Double or Integer, and a method to process a string representation of an object.

    The checkDouble and checkInteger methods return boolean values indicating whether the object can be parsed to the respective types. The checkString method processes the string by removing escape characters and quotes. 

     
 TypeChecker typeChecker = new TypeChecker();
 boolean isDouble = typeChecker.checkDouble("123.45");
 boolean isInteger = typeChecker.checkInteger("123");
 String processedString = typeChecker.checkString("\"Hello, World!\"");

      • checkString

        public java.lang.String checkString(java.lang.Object o)
        Processes the string representation of the given object by removing escape characters and quotes.

        If the string is empty after processing, it returns the empty string. If any error occurs during processing, it prints an error message using Messages.ERROR() and returns null.

        Parameters:
        o - the object to be processed
        Returns:
        the processed string, or null if an error occurs
